# Create & Manage a Campaign in Dynamics 365 (Sales)

---

## 1. High-Level Overview

### What this is  
A **campaign** is how you plan, run, and track a marketing effort in Dynamics 365.  

It connects:
- Your **target audience** (marketing lists)  
- Your **activities** (emails, calls, tasks)  
- Your **results** (responses, costs, performance)

### Why it matters (for sales)  
- Keeps outreach organised instead of scattered  
- Helps you track what’s working (and what isn’t)  
- Aligns sales and marketing on the same activity  

### What problem it solves  
Without campaigns, outreach is random and hard to track.  
With campaigns, everything sits in one place: audience, actions, and results.  [oai_citation:0‡Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/is-is/dynamics365/sales/create-edit-campaign-using-app-marketing-sales?utm_source=chatgpt.com)  

---

## 2. Word Glossary

| Term | Simple Meaning |
|-----|------|
| Campaign | A planned set of sales/marketing activities |
| Campaign Activity | A specific action (e.g. email, call, task) |
| Planning Activity | Prep work before launch (e.g. create content) |
| Marketing List | The audience you are targeting |
| Channel | How you contact people (email, phone, etc.) |
| Budget | Planned cost of the campaign |
| Response Rate | How many people engage or reply |

**Important:**  
- A **campaign = the container**  
- Activities = what you actually *do*  

---

## 3. Quick Wins / Need to Know

- Campaign = **plan + audience + actions + tracking**
- You must attach at least **one marketing list**
- Activities are where the real work happens (calls, emails)
- Campaigns track **costs and performance**
- Large campaigns can take time to send (not instant)  [oai_citation:1‡Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/is-is/dynamics365/sales/create-edit-campaign-using-app-marketing-sales?utm_source=chatgpt.com)  

